<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?>
<!DOCTYPE plist PUBLIC "-//Apple//DTD PLIST 1.0//EN" "http://www.apple.com/DTDs/PropertyList-1.0.dtd">
<!--
  App entitlements for the "Open Magi" Tauri shell (the outer .app).

  This is the Rust/WKWebView host process. It is deliberately MINIMAL: an empty
  entitlements dictionary under the Hardened Runtime, i.e. the shell requests NO
  security exceptions for itself.

  Why empty and not the sidecar's exceptions:
    - The JIT / unsigned-executable-memory / library-validation exceptions are
      needed by the frozen-Python child process, NOT by this shell. Those
      exceptions apply per-process, and the sidecar is a separately signed
      executable with its own entitlements (see entitlements.sidecar.plist), so
      the shell does not need to inherit or relax anything to launch it.
    - WKWebView runs page JavaScript in a separate system-provided WebContent
      process with its own entitlements; the shell itself does not JIT.
    - Keeping this file empty preserves the strongest Hardened Runtime posture
      for the shell that Gatekeeper / notarization will accept.

  Referenced by tauri.conf.json -> bundle.macOS.entitlements. Tauri applies it
  when it signs the outer .app during `cargo tauri build`.
-->
<plist version="1.0">
  <dict/>
</plist>
